    {
      "id": "f9f7564be2010ff6c0c2d773331827dd3a04ddd0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 308,
        "name": "Amir Shehata",
        "email": "ashehata@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ashehata"
      },
      "date": "2018-04-04 01:37:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nYou don't want to delete the peer if it's a gateway under any circumstances. The gateway peer is removed when you delete the route. What's the problem you're trying to address with this patch?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "144219ea8c0e4b5a57e039ba24de7e1ee01bb4e3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 659,
        "name": "Sonia Sharma",
        "email": "sharmaso@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "sharmaso"
      },
      "date": "2018-04-04 02:14:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> (1 comment)\n > \n > You don't want to delete the peer if it's a gateway under any\n > circumstances. The gateway peer is removed when you delete the\n > route. What's the problem you're trying to address with this patch?\n\nIn lnet_del_peer_nid(), \n\n > (1 comment)\n > \n > You don't want to delete the peer if it's a gateway under any\n > circumstances. The gateway peer is removed when you delete the\n > route. What's the problem you're trying to address with this patch?\n\nIn lnet_del_peer_nid(), lnet_peer_ni_del_locked is called without taking its return value. So if this function returns with -EBUSY, lnet_del_peer_nid()  still returns with 0 which hides -EBUSY error.\n\nWith this patch, I am checking the return value of lnet_peer_ni_del_locked to see if it was a success or an errro",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "20187d2458ec06c85fc52ac446e8ecb97d433ccf",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 659,
        "name": "Sonia Sharma",
        "email": "sharmaso@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "sharmaso"
      },
      "date": "2018-04-04 02:31:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\n> (1 comment)\n > \n > You don't want to delete the peer if it's a gateway under any\n > circumstances. The gateway peer is removed when you delete the\n > route. What's the problem you're trying to address with this patch?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
